sequenceDiagram
    actor "Client Contact Browser" as ClientContactBrowser
    participant "Frontend Web Application" as FrontendWebApplication
    participant "Backend API" as BackendAPI
    participant "PostgreSQL Database" as PostgreSQLDatabase
    participant "AWS SES" as AWSSES

    activate FrontendWebApplication
    ClientContactBrowser->>FrontendWebApplication: 1. 1. GET /approve/milestone/{jwt}
    FrontendWebApplication-->>ClientContactBrowser: 8. Returns server-side rendered HTML page
    activate BackendAPI
    FrontendWebApplication->>BackendAPI: 2. 2. [SSR] GET /api/v1/public/milestones/review/{jwt}
    BackendAPI-->>FrontendWebApplication: 7. Returns 200 OK with milestone details
    BackendAPI->>BackendAPI: 3. 3. Validate JWT (Signature, Expiry, Type)
    BackendAPI-->>BackendAPI: Validation result
    activate PostgreSQLDatabase
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 4. 4. SELECT ... FROM Milestones m JOIN ApprovalTokens t ON m.Id = t.MilestoneId WHERE t.Jti = {jwt.jti} AND t.UsedAt IS NULL
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: 6. Returns Milestone & Project data
    BackendAPI->>BackendAPI: 5. 5. Check if token JTI exists and is unused
    ClientContactBrowser->>BackendAPI: 9. 9. POST /api/v1/public/milestones/approve/{jwt}
    BackendAPI-->>ClientContactBrowser: 18. Returns 200 OK { success: true }
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 10. 10. BEGIN TRANSACTION
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: 14. COMMIT TRANSACTION
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 11. 11. SELECT ... FROM ApprovalTokens WHERE Jti = {jwt.jti} FOR UPDATE
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Token record
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 12. 12. UPDATE Milestones SET Status = 'Approved' WHERE Id = {milestoneId}
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Rows affected
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 13. 13. UPDATE ApprovalTokens SET UsedAt = NOW() WHERE Jti = {jwt.jti}
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Rows affected
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 14. 14. INSERT INTO AuditLogs (Action, Entity, ...)
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: New record ID
    activate AWSSES
    BackendAPI->>AWSSES: 15. 15. [Async] Send 'Milestone Approved' email to Admin
    AWSSES-->>BackendAPI: 16. Returns 200 OK
    FrontendWebApplication->>ClientContactBrowser: 19. 19. Update UI to display confirmation message

    note over BackendAPI: AC-002: If 'action' is 'REJECT', the POST body must include a 'reason' string. The API validates ...
    note over BackendAPI: AC-003 & AC-004: If the token is expired (based on JWT 'exp' claim) or already used (based on 'Us...
    note over BackendAPI: AC-005: Any malformed JWT or invalid signature will fail step 3 and result in an HTTP 400 or 403 ...

    deactivate AWSSES
    deactivate PostgreSQLDatabase
    deactivate BackendAPI
    deactivate FrontendWebApplication
